				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Note: the headlines that I saw said &quot;The US under Attack&quot;<BR>
It wasn't really the US that declared the war if you think about it. It was whomever made the first attack that declared it.<BR>
<BR>
---------<BR>
Next: continuation of my earlier mention about the criminal justice system...<BR>
<BR>
These &quot;dogs of war&quot; are not unleashed... they are being given a target.  Thier job is to investigate the situation, solve who dunit, and then go make thier arrest. It is up to the suspects to answer thier court summons... <BR>
Once again:<BR>
<BR>
Bin Ladin has REJECTED his court summons, therefore they are gonna arrest him/ protect themselves while doing it if he retaliates further toward his arrest.<BR>
<BR>
Bin Ladin appears to be trying to get as many other people to fall for his &quot;I'm innocent&quot; line as he can and he is gonna try to have them stand up and say that he has no need to fight the evidence in court because he says that he is innocent. Unless he goes to court of his own free will, his actions now and his possible actions in the future will be used against him and they will be used as an admission of guilt.  If Bin Ladin really wants to save his butt (assuming that he is innocent)and not have a bunch of other ignorant people get killed, he will answer his court summons accordingly and agree to a hearing.<BR>
<BR>
BTW: we have not yet reached the amount of news broadcasts that were sent out on JFKs assasination.. that one went on for longer than 2 weeks.<BR>

