			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				/bonk myself in the head...<BR>
<BR>
Yep i deserved that, that's what you get for trying to write a coherent post at 2am. What i meant to say was...<BR>
<BR>
They have unleashed the Dogs of War without a target......<BR>
<BR>
As for the US 'meddling', I have no problem with the US doing something about preventing it from happening again, I just don't like how it has all been shoved in the rest of the world's face because it happened to the US. This notion of the US 'Declaring War' is just stupid and hypocritical.<BR>
<BR>
Take Israel for example. They get suicide bombed all the time. Yet whenever they try to retaliate (let alone 'Declare War') the UN, largely US controlled, frowns on them. In times past UN nations have even stopped selling them arms because of their retaliations (leading to such wonders as the Desert Eagle and the Uzi =).<BR>
But now its perfectly fine for the US to not only retaliate but also declare war? Am I the only one to see a double standard?
				</font>
